{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01T16Xyind7LUc9UtVjuEKFS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the source file and convert it to a knowledge file JSON.\n\n**Step 1: Identify the title**\nThe first heading underlined with `=====` is:\n\"送信ボタンやリンクを押すと、IEでのみ「オブジェクトでサポートされていないプロパティまたはメソッドです」と表示され画面が遷移しません。\"\n\n**Step 1.5: Check for no-knowledge-content**\nThe source has actual content (a Q&A about IE issues with form element names). This contains Layer A content (constraints about name attributes). Set `no_knowledge_content: false`.\n \nNow I'm looking at the document structure—there are no subsections, just the main heading with a single Q&A block. The question describes an IE-specific error when clicking submit buttons or links, and the answer identifies that this occurs when a form element has \"submit\" as its name attribute.\n\nThe root cause is a naming collision between FORM object methods and properties with the name attributes of form elements. This affects Internet Explorer versions 6 through 8 and older Firefox versions. The fix is straightforward: rename the problematic name attribute to something else. The answer also includes a list of name attribute values that should be avoided entirely. I'm showing the corrected JSP code where the problematic `name=\"submit\"` attribute gets changed to `name=\"register\"` to avoid conflicts with the form object's built-in methods, then listing the reserved attribute values that should never be used in IE and older Firefox versions.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20759,"cache_read_input_tokens":29955,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20759,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2b6ae08d-2c1d-4f7e-95b4-41474598ecc7","uuid":"be6f50d7-3c60-4000-aef1-178cc4c